<subSubSection id="C358655E860C6B2AFAE089D2F799F86E" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFAE089D2F880F928" blockId="30.[1288,2267,1446,1899]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">
Remarks. This genus is introduced for the first time to the Australian fauna to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AF7F289A0F92BF9B2" authority="Yoo, 1988" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Loxonema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegantissima">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AF7F289A0FA77F9B2" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Loxonema elegantissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24860C6B2AFA248A76F92BF9B2" author="Yoo, E. K." box="[1532,1713,1538,1577]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" pagination="233 - 264" refId="ref27552" refString="Yoo, E. K., 1988. Early Carboniferous Mollusca from Gundy, Upper Hunter, New South Wales. Records of the Australian Museum 40 (4): 233 - 264." type="journal article" year="1988">Yoo, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AF91E8A76F7AEF9B2" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1734,2100,1538,1577]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gundyensis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AF91E8A76F7AEF9B2" box="[1734,2100,1538,1577]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis gundyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860C6B2AF79A8A76F714F9B2" box="[2114,2190,1538,1577]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFAD08A5BFA34F9CC" authorityName="Meek" authorityYear="1872" box="[1288,1454,1583,1623]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFAD08A5BFA34F9CC" box="[1288,1454,1583,1623]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFA2F8A5BF800F9CC" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" box="[1527,1946,1583,1623]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Loxonema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegantissima">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFA2F8A5BF800F9CC" box="[1527,1946,1583,1623]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Loxonema elegantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFA288A29F90DF91E" authorityName="Meek" authorityYear="1872" box="[1520,1687,1629,1669]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFA288A29F90DF91E" box="[1520,1687,1629,1669]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its minute shell with strong sinuous collabral lirae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFAE08ACDF928F8F0" blockId="30.[1288,2267,1446,1899]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">
Australian Carboniferous species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AF7FA8ACDF903F894" authority="(Yoo)" baseAuthorityName="Yoo" baseAuthorityYear="1988" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegantissima">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AF7FA8ACDF99EF894" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis elegantissima</emphasis>
(Yoo)
</taxonomicName>
, from 'Marohn'; 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AF7F98A93FA5AF8A6" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gundyensis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AF7F98A93FA5AF8A6" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis gundyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860C6B2AFA0C8B61F9BEF8A6" box="[1492,1572,1813,1853]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from 'Marohn'; 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AF8BB8B61F793F8A6" authorityName="Meek" authorityYear="1872" box="[1891,2057,1813,1853]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AF8BB8B61F793F8A6" box="[1891,2057,1813,1853]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (in this study), from 'Kyndalyn'.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFA068BBAF799F86E" blockId="30.[1502,2051,1998,2037]" box="[1502,2051,1998,2037]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFA068BBAF799F86E" baseAuthorityName="Yoo" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1502,2051,1998,2037]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Streptacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegantissima">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFA068BBAF810F86E" box="[1502,1930,1998,2037]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Streptacis elegantissima</emphasis>
